Auction! Pilchuck green double leaf pendant 🌿 aloha everyone, sorry it’s been a while! I’m still processing my awesome summer vacation and recovering from it as well 😉 this beauty was made for one of my demos during @vitrovixen’s class at @pilchuckglassschool last session. What a beautiful place even without any glasswork, the color green is everywhere in about a million different shades. Green can be tricky to make unique in glass as it has its own issues in chemistry and color tones or lack thereof so I’ve had to endlessly experiment with different layering combinations. I hope to teach a class about boro color at pilchuck someday! Signed and dated with pilchuck written below to show what a special piece this is for me, I rarely write anything else on a piece. My brand new stickers included as well! To bid please note my comment that will state “Bid Here”, all bids must be placed as a reply to this comment to keep them in order. Dm me with any questions please!!🌿🌈 Size - 2" wide X 3" tall X 1/2" deep

Rules
1️⃣No starting bid, bids must be placed as a reply to my “Bid Here” comment. 
2️⃣Bidding increments of at least $10 please 
3️⃣Must be 18 years or older to bid 
4️⃣Shipping is $10 for US
5️⃣Please let me know if you are going to have me ship this across a border. 
6️⃣Must be ready to pay immediately by PayPal only, no exceptions!!! Non payment in 24 hours from the closing of auction will get you banned!!!
7️⃣Bidding ends when I call it around  24 hours after posting this photo. I will tag and repost hours before ending. 
Please feel free to dm me with questions. 
Happy bidding!

Finished Red Tailed Tropicbird sculpture. NFS. I was asked to make a commission with seabirds from Hawaii. I chose these beautiful birds and made a background representing the mountains, the coastal waters and the deep ocean. These birds nest in the cliffs, sometimes far inland and on the steepest inclines and then hunt out at see for squid that come up from the deep ocean. You can see several species of Tropicbirds throughout Hawaii, try the Kilauea lighthouse on Kaua’i to see for them for yourself! #flamework #flameworking #lampwork #lampworking #glass #redtailedtropicbird #tropicbird #bird #headyart #glassofig #highshelfglass #borosilicate #borofauna

.

I believe it was Indigo, Carbon Black, Ultra Violet, and fine Halo (holographic) glitter.

'Interdimensional Portal to Infinity # 8' ... The process of creating this helped me to transcend time as I fed a campfire & photographed the energetic release of smoke and embers as spirits danced around the burning logs - capturing the motion of the flames was an awe-inspiring process and the still photos are wonderful, but, I still felt like I had to do some remixing in order to truly add my energy into the mix. This fiery portal is meant transport the viewer to a place of peace inside their mind as they stare deeply into the patterns of flames engulfing themselves & re-emerge endlessly into Infinity. ... I know this one is less complex than most of the portals but...I lost my phone recently & I lost a ton of my clips that were made to be used for lengthier & more detailed animations as well as the application I used for stringing the clips together. While I'm still looking for a new software which renders in 1080p; I wanted to share this piece of my meditation, since it brought me so much joy to create.

“Sometimes you got to get through your fear to see the beauty on the other side”⁣ - Poppa (The Good Dinosaur)⁣
⁣
Brontosaurus’ have always been my favorite dinosaur 🤗⁣
⁣
One of the first headies I ever hit was an Elbo Bronto at the 2015 High Times Cannabis Cup 🌳🔥💨⁣
⁣
As soon as I got into glass I knew I wanted to make one myself but I wanted to wait until I could make a unique version. ⁣ ⁣
After seeing the movie, The Good Dinosaur, I was inspired to make one based off of Arlo and his family 🦕 ⁣
⁣
This is my second one to date and I am extremely happy with it. ⁣
⁣
I used Shamrock and Chartreuse from @glassalchemy which were surprisingly easy for me to work with on my Herbie 🌈⁣
⁣
He’s nearly 6“ tall and has a 10mm joint 📏⁣
⁣
He is in need of a home! 🏡 ⁣
⁣

🔥🔥🔥 @dadneedsdabs showing that sometimes even the most simple of caps, can add the world of difference to your dab! I’ve seen LOTS of messed up bubble caps; Egg shaped, wrong size, or just downright fragile. The weird thing is sometimes these same bubble caps are the ones in store shelves for $50+! Sure, maybe I could charge more for me caps. Heck, maybe I could even outsource them and put my name on them right..? Sure, I could, but then I wouldn’t be any better than those guys. I take an immense amount of pride in doing things myself, the right way. I make caps I would take home, and toss the ones that I wouldn’t. Period. Maybe I’m losing money not charging more, or mass producing them, or by hiding seconds in my firsts. But I sleep great at night knowing each cap that is purchased from me... whether it’s a simple $39.99 bubble cap or a $500+ Auction custom, is gonna work exactly how it should. If you’re using my caps, thank you. Quartz Crystal Point .
.
When I saw this quartz point in one of the rock shops last weekend, I knew it needed to be set with a spessartine garnet. The layers that are included in this crystal are amazing. I wish my camera could capture the depth in this stone! The garnet's natural facets bring out the orange inclusions in the quartz. I then added two faceted smoky quartz to bring the piece to the warm, "fall like" side of the color wheel. 🍂
.
.

"Repurposed Rats"
.
.
These were some of the first skulls I ever made so they are FULL of fuck ups! All the details I tried to sculpt just caused acute angles leading to large cracks, and I didn't know what flame to use for this color, so there are boiled bits all over lol!😹 I picked up this frame a couple weeks ago and decided to put these little rats in it to remind me of where I started and how even though I had no idea what I was doing in the beginning, I still just went for it. A little reminder to be fearless and to relearn how to take risks⚡
.
